Step 1: Identify the quick assets. Quick assets include:
 • Cash on Hand = 4,863,237.11
 • Bank Deposits = 3,502,535.57
 • Interest Receivable = 11,346.19
 • Accounts Receivable = 1,454,443.80

Step 2: Sum up the quick assets.
 Total Quick Assets = 4,863,237.11 + 3,502,535.57 + 11,346.19 + 1,454,443.80 = 9,831,562.67

Step 3: Identify the current liabilities.
 Total Current Liabilities (End_amount) = 1,548,001.20

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio.
 Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities
 Quick Ratio = 9,831,562.67 / 1,548,001.20 ≈ 6.35

Thus, the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is approximately 6.35.
